Cream together white sugar, brown sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla, peanut butter and the egg. Add in flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Wrap 1 heaping teaspoon of dough around a bite sized milk chocolate covered caramel and nougat candy bar. Bake 13-16 minutes at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.